tip.text: Must say what a great place to chill and get some latin cuisine overdose. Desserts were heavenly, cayenne ice cream with chocolate fondant and churros! OMG!
Soba sandwich time!
Cake selection is extensive. But it falls short on taste. Too dense, too heavy. Couldn't finish my dark chocolate cake slice.
Although paul's staff is known for being extremely friendly, this branch tops it all. As usual i cant resist their pain perdu and espresso ;)
A less pricy option to have some good mana'eesh. Kafta with cheese, labneh, kashkaval and za3tar taste really nice.
The food is not so great and a bit pricy. Small slice of moussaka for 110dhs. Chicken pita was blend. Waiter was unattentive and kept mixing up our orders. Not coming back.

So impressed with the amount of hard work and creativity. Amazing decoration and concept, felt like i was really in alice in wonderland film!the cafe of forgotten objects and eye spies rooms r surreal

formattedAddress: Mall of the Emirates (Sheikh Zayed Rd)

tip.text: Finally this amazing taiwanese chain opened in dubai! Menu is slightly different, nevertheless great! Go for szechuan veg&chicken wontons, special chilli noodles, xiao long bao, taro bun!yummmy!!!

formattedAddress: Mall of the Emirates (Sheikh Zayed Rd)

tip.text: This branch is cozier and staff is a bit less arrogant than the one in dubai mall. Still, i dont recommend mont blanc for dessert. Onion soup is very tasty.
Seats are comfortable and its not too crowded. Go for 4dx experience! You wont regret it!

formattedAddress: Mall of the Emirates (Sheikh Zayed Rd)

tip.text: Good enough for a quick bite, yet nothing about this place is authentic, food is too heavy. Bulgogi is a bit salty but good, scallion pancake is ok, rice cake is unedible, taste like rubber.
Nice new yet extremely quiet steakhouse towards the end of jbr. Go for bbq ribs and merguez sausages.
Couldnt decide which slice i wanted, so i took all of them. Love the honey, mille feuille and roll cake. Just the right amount of richness. Highly recommend it!
Not the greatest pizza, yet always fun to come here and make your own pizza. Careful with the add ons though, or your pizza mind end up costing you 10x more than in a 5 star resto.

formattedAddress: Mall of The Emirates (Sheikh Zayed Road)

tip.text: Best friday brunch ever! Been coming here for 2yrs and it just gets better! Selection mains and desserts are superb. Staff very attentive and friendly.

location.address: West Crescent Road, The Palm Jumeirah
formattedAddress: West Crescent Road, The Palm Jumeirah (Jumeirah Zabeel Saray)

tip.text: Just spent my nye there. Nice place, event was well organized. Had a great time!!
tiki puka puka all the way! love this place!
Always crowded this branch , nevertheless good coffee and brie cheese omelette is just yummy.

formattedAddress: Rimal, The Walk, Dubai (Jumeirah Beach Residence)
Rimal, The Walk, Dubai (Jumeirah Beach Residence)

tip.text: Always good always a good treat coming to this place. Aprong rolls, dumplings je and gai superb to start with. Pad kee mao for main. Just delightful!
Love the quattro formaggi pizza, not the best but i enjoyed every bite! Adding to it, by far the funniest and friendliest staff i've met in dubai. Great job, keep it up!!
Finally mikado opened in dubai!! Everything is delicious here! Doriyaki and melon pan were light yet delicious!
Great place! Highly recommend 4dx movie experience. Illy coffee shop available as well. What i could ask for more? :)
Leila is one those lebanese places that make u feel right at home. Cheese rolls, samboosek, fattoush, hommous and the grills were just as great as the one in beirut.
Everything is good here! Muhalla, regag, balaleet. Aaah also the seasoned fries and samboosa cheese. Sweetest end ever with lugaimat!! Love this place!!!
Beautiful funky place to be and eat at! Lemon pie tastes really nice, giving that amazingly sour tingly feeling in every bite.
How can i put in words without sounding too rude? Everything tastes non italian. Food tastes like the owner likes it to. Dont waste ur time n money here.
Labneh with olives is just perfect for me always. I recommend kafta and kashkaval as well.
Great option for breakfast in jlt! French toast is really good!
Was in the mood for a slice of marble boston cake...where else but coco's!yum yum
Pizza is soooooo goooooood. Love the staff and service! Salentina pizza my fav.
Acai and caju juice at the beach yay! As a brazilian i can say its not the best yet good enough for a nice day at the beach ;)
If you need some peace n quiet from the chaos in the malls during summer, this is one of the places to check out. Good variety of restaurants n coffee shops.
To say this is the best turkish place is blasphemy. Neither i nor my friends could eat the meat. Not coming back.

venue.name: Sultan Baba İskender سلطان بابا إسكندر

tip.text: Early breakfast today. Had mini croissants selection and a latte. hmmm nothing special about it.

formattedAddress: Atlantis The Palm (Crescent Road, Palm Island)

tip.text: Always love staying here...quiet, clean, fast srvc and friendly staff.  Breakfast is ok.
A good lebanese rest is known by its hommous. Great food, fast service, friendly staff. I recommend grilled half chicken. Tender and full in flavor.
Paris breast custard...soooooooo good!
Cafe latte is always good here. Tried red velvet cake also... Hmm better off to stick just to the coffee.
good quality burgers and fries

location.address: Dubai Mall, 1st Floor, Near The Waterfall
formattedAddress: Dubai Mall, 1st Floor, Near The Waterfall (The Dubai Mall)

tip.text: Cozy place in barsha, very homy. Chicken dimsums and koi theyo noodles with veggies. Nice! Coming back for sure!

formattedAddress: Al Barsha Business Square (Al Barsha St 1)

tip.text: Same as all malls, but extremely busy and noisy.
so many favorites here thats impossible to count them! La capresina piadine, burrata panino, mozzarella in carrozza, bocconcini di mozzarella, the bianca pizza and much more! everything tastes great!
Impossible to have a cake instore and too hot outside. No problem!!!Rainbow and brooklyn blackout cake for take away pls :)
Not like it used to be, but ill still come back for my kraft with honey fatayer mushaltat.
My favorite bookstore. Got my mangas! (^_^)
Wanted to try this place for a while, must say it was rather disappointing. Gemista and moussaka were a bit heavy and chicken skewer was raw. Not coming back.
Love this place! Pizza time!
Too crowded too noisy, yet the strawberry mille feuille compensates it all :)
Iced latte time! Yum!

formattedAddress: Mall Of the Emirates (Next to Centrepoint)

tip.text: Nutella cinnabon! OMG!
Fried mac n cheese, corn hotdogs and tater tots for appetizers. Bbq pulled beef sandwich for mains was ok. Last but not least godiva cheesecake...oh yeah ;)

location.address: The Beach, The Walk, Jumeirah Beach Residence
formattedAddress: The Beach, The Walk, Jumeirah Beach Residence

tip.text: Smoked beef chuck rib is very tender with chips and snickers bar for dessert is simply sublime.
Found bumblebee! Great movies great place el capitan!
Aaaand its just a sign :P
Try the brazilian restaurant samba right at the entrance

formattedAddress: 100 Universal City Plaza (btwn Barham Blvd & Lankershim Blvd)

tip.text: Check out trastevere restaurant, great italian food.  There's also a very nice club called OHM.
Red velvet was a bit heavy.
Superman and Tatsu!!! Best rides ever! Love this place.
Pad see ew and kee mao noodles are simply delicious.

formattedAddress: 5900 Hollywood Blvd Ste B (at N Bronson Ave)

tip.text: Sushi and the soba were ok, great for a quick bite.
so much fuuuuuuuun here! transformers ride was amazing! Best ride by far! Avoid weekends.

formattedAddress: 100 Universal City Plz (btwn Barham Blvd & Lankershim Blvd)

tip.text: One word: yummy!!!
Good selection of toppings. The dough is not heavy, all on all its a good pizza place.

formattedAddress: 2 E Colorado Blvd (at Fair Oaks Ave)

tip.text: Looks like more of meet up place.

formattedAddress: 54 West Colorado Boulevard (btw De Lacey & Fair Oaks)

tip.text: Just love it!! the shops, people, food and drinks... Wouldn't mind coming here everyday
Truffle fries, tempura onion rings and sunny side burger... Delicious!
Chicken shawarma and kebab are delightful, bread and hummus just amazing. Must try :)
What a place! Spectacular! Best bookstore i've been to.
Amaaaaaaazing view!
Beautiful cozy and nice people... Luv this town!
Great service! Amazing pizza.What a perfect ending to a night! Coming back for sure!
Mickey mouse and michael jackson stars found! Mission accomplished! Luv this place!!!
Friendly staff in this branch :)
Great for breakfast! Sweet mexican breads are heavenly!
The best!!! Castella is soooo goooood!
Nice sandwiches. Caprese is very good. Great for a quick bite in jlt.
Can't find anything good to say... Avoid it
What to say about karam that hasn't been said? Amazing delicious lebanese food no matter which branch. Thumbs up! Super friendly staff ;)
Oooh man ohhh man ooooh my god amazing donuts! Old fashioned and vanilla deluxe donuts are simply heavenly!!!!
Just plain ordinary chinese food. Great for a quick bite. Hofun beef noodles, veg dumplings and bao are good.
Club sandwich and cafe latte were good. Try the pina colada cake, super yummy!!

location.address: Tower B, Business Central Towers, Dubai Media City
formattedAddress: Tower B, Business Central Towers, Dubai Media City (Sheikh Zayed Rd)

tip.text: Good for cheese, cold cuts and wine get together. Live band is not as good as it used to be. Best for couples.

location.address: The Westin Dubai Mina Seyahi Beach Resort & Marina,
formattedAddress: The Westin Dubai Mina Seyahi Beach Resort & Marina,

tip.text: Pain perdu... We meet again! love you!!! ❤️
Always so so so busy this branch. Try the hazelnut eclair and brownie, yummy yummy ;)

location.address: Mall of the Emirates, Dubai(Ground Floor)
formattedAddress: Mall of the Emirates, Dubai(Ground Floor)

tip.text: Cafe latte is good. Mus try the dutch pancakes!

location.address: Dubai Marina Mall, opposite Yo Sushi
formattedAddress: Dubai Marina Mall, opposite Yo Sushi

tip.text: By far better than the branch in ibn battuta mall. The staff was extremely friendy. Great for a quick bite. Beware, portions are massive. Singapore noodles and wok seared tenserloin were ok.
Great food, nice live music. Pizza and pasta selection is very good, so is the wine selection. Good for a romantic dinner :)
Velvet cake yes pls gimme more!!! Very moist and light. Other options are kitkat and caramel cheesecake. For those who live in jlt its a good fix ;)
Food is good but not great. Extremely overpriced for a pizza place. 5 cheese and porcini pizzas were nice. For starter focaccia aglio e olio, el cupppo tradizionale and la mozzatta.
Simit kashkaval sandwich, that's new and it tastes good. Oh yes and my beloved cafe latte ;)
Love this mall. I can spend a whole day in it and not get bored!

formattedAddress: Mohammed bin Rashid Blvd. (بوليفارد محمد بن راشد)

tip.text: Nice place for meeting up with friends and family over coffee and nice dessert. Go for dhibs millefeuille and chocolate fondant, you won't regret it!
My favorite branch! Fast service, amazing friendly staff. Calzone quatro formaggi is light and tomato base tastes great. Rosemary potato, tomato n pesto bread, bruschetta for starters.
Manti is ok, perde pilav and haslama kofte were very saucy and tasty. Peynirli pide and lahmacun are a must. The best of all is the kunefe filled with tender cheese and pistachio, not too sweet.
Chewy melts and cronuts are amazing. Although almoat everything tastes great!!
From the name i thought i'd get some innovative method in eating shawarma, but its just another shawarma joint. Chicken and beef shawarma sandwiches were both dry, very small and blend.

formattedAddress: Al Barsha B (البرشاء، نفس مبنى ستاربكس)

tip.text: Good service but the food overall is mediocre and overpriced. Don't recommend it.
bao is ok and so was the nasi goreng. Service is really slow though. Thai sticky rice with mango is good.
Definitely the best turkish restaurant in dubai. Lahmacoun, doner and pide are heavenly!

formattedAddress: Jumeirah Road, Next to Spinneys (شارع جميرا - بجوار سبينيس)

tip.text: Ordering coffee instead of tea might be considered as blasphemy here. Either way im a coffee not tea person. The cakes taste great and are very light. Try the afternoon tea option :)

formattedAddress: The Dubai Mall (Mohammed Bin Rashed Boulevard)

tip.text: Bang bang chicken and crispy chili honey potato not bad. Thai green curry with beef and bami goreng were ok. Thai sticky rice with mango and custard buns for dessert ok.
Burrata with truffle oil is simply super delicious, melts in your mouth. Besides that, its just another ordinary pizza place. Pizza is bland and tiramisu is too sweet.

venue.name: OBICÀ Mozzarella Bar & Pizza E Cucina

tip.text: Gyoza ok, karaage ok, zaru soba ok. Ramen forget it, lost my hope in dubai...only in japan u'll get the authentic one.
Best place to find great bargains and then head out for best and cheapest food. Steamed pork buns for me pls :)
Love all buns!! Coconut bun, cheese bun, melon bun and the mini soft cheesecake yum:)
Cream bread and cheese bread and all the other breads :)))
Love the brazilian cheese buns.
The ramen tastes good, pork cutlets super tender. Fast service.
Pafu pafu, cheese bread all is good! Yum yum ;)

location.address: #B1-29 The Central, 6 Eu Tong Sen St.
formattedAddress: #B1-29 The Central, 6 Eu Tong Sen St. (Tew Chew St.)

tip.text: Custard mini donuts... Yummmmmmyyyy ;)
Cheese and custard are my favs!
One of my favorite bakeries, love the baumkuchen!

formattedAddress: 391 Orchard Road Takashimaya B2 205 3-1 (Food Hall B2)

tip.text: Amazing variety if food and sweets in one place, but finding a table to eat is a mission impossible .

formattedAddress: B2, Ngee Ann City Takashimaya (391 Orchard Rd.)

tip.text: Buns were dry but the caramel toast was good enough.
Sesame pretzel is the best. Having the original one now... Yummy yummy!!
Overpriced, but the millefeuille is very good.
Nice outdoor seating. Coconut pie my fav! German cake is also good.

formattedAddress: The Beach, JBR (الشاطئ - جيه بي آر)

tip.text: Arouss labne, kashkawan and kafta manakeesh are the best.
Love the labneh and cream cheese with olives bagels.
Always come here when im homesick. Brigadeiro cake is good ;)

location.address: JLT, Cluster U, Al Seef Tower 2
formattedAddress: JLT, Cluster U, Al Seef Tower 2 (lake front)

tip.text: Morning, afternoon or night... Anytime is a good time for pancakes at ihop! The best :)
Avoid it. Unedible pizza, dough too tough to bite or cut thru.
Tried the red velvet whoopie pie, very dry and cream cheese is heavy. Dunno whats all the hype about this place.
If u live in jlt and want a japanese quick fix, otherwise avoid it. Omusoba not bad
Japanese fast food, ok for a quick bite.
Love the buns!!
Nice tapas restaurant, great staff, great ambience all in all! the complimentary side bread with dips is to die for! chorizo is yummy as well as the traditional omelette, paella and churros

formattedAddress: Al Qasr Hotel Madinat Jumeirah (Al Sufouh Rd)

tip.text: Best egg tarts!

venue.name: Tong Heng Confectionery 東興餅家

tip.text: Melon pan my favorite!

formattedAddress: B2-03, Takashimaya Food Hall (391A Orchard Rd)

tip.text: great place, tried a bit from everything as always ;)
love this patisserie! Original mille crepe, oreo, cappuccino luv all
coconut egg custard, yummy!
amazing breads, cheesecake, pafu pafu... yumminess!
love love love everything at bread talk!
Many things to try here, everything is so yummy! There's arancine, spiedini di mozzarella, the bianca pizza with extra prosciutto...ending with chocolate terrine...heavenly!
couldn't decide which piece to try...bought few, hazelnut cake is great

location.address: L1-03, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands
formattedAddress: L1-03, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands (2 Bayfront Avenue)

tip.text: Good thai food, must try the clay pot chicken with black mushroom and sticky rice with mango
good asian dining restaurant, green curry chicken and bakmi goreng are my favs!
The best and only japanese bakery in town. Selection of breads not so big, but melon and custard bun is definitely my fav!
The best coffee ever! Nothing can beat illy coffee
Great pizza, burrata cheese also good as a starter.
Beat for breakfast or brunch. The eggs benedict are my fav!
Best cinnamon pancakes in town!
The food is great! A lot of cheese on the menu, perfect for cheese lovers like me. Nothing can beat the French fries though!
Great meat, desserts and atmosphere is superb! I always go for the burger and fondant for dessert
Great japanese dept store, visit the food village in the basement, amazing food!
Good bargains, cheap and vast option for best street food :)
I love singapore! Everything about this country is great!
Good italian food, staff is extremely friendly, cozy environment. Tomato and pesto bread is to die for! Pizza n pasta also great! Must try!
Everything about this place is great! The food, music, staff and environment just perfect! Perfect for a date or dinner n drinks with friends :)

location.address: Level 1, Souk Al Bahar, Burj Khalifa Area
formattedAddress: Level 1, Souk Al Bahar, Burj Khalifa Area (Sheikh Zayed Rd)

tip.text: Good desserts, fav is german chocolate cake and coconut almond bars
Great food, friendly staff! Outdoor seating is a better choice, wagyu beef is simply amazing!
Best thai food in dubai! Must try!!! Desserts are amazing: bangkok moji and kao neaw mamuang highly recommended,
Pizza is my absolutely my fav! The view is amazing, great for a date, staff is very friendly

formattedAddress: The Westin Dubai Mina Seyahi (Al Sufouh Rd)

tip.text: The coffee, pastries and desserts are highly recommended ;) my favorite is the pain perdu, simply yummy!!

formattedAddress: Jumeirah Beach Residence, JBR Walk (ممشى الجي بي آر)

tip.text: The desserts are good and it has a relaxing atmosphere ;)
Great food! For starters we ordered the mini pitas, baked cheese, braised artichoke and the famous crispy manti.For mains i recommend begendi and yoghurt kebab. Ah last but not least, choco souffle!
